{
  "texts": [
    "Hence, β = 0 in this case.",
    "From Hitchin's desciption [Hit87, Prop.",
    "10.2] of the moduli space of SL 2 (R)-Higgs bundles, we obtain the following description of N d, 0 < d ≤ g -1.Proposition 5.1 (Hitchin,[Hit87]).",
    "For a fixed Riemann surface Σ = (B 2, c) and an integer d ∈ (0, g -1], the set N d is a 2 2g -fold covering of S r B, where r = 2g -2 -2d.Here, S r B is the r-th symmetric product of B.",
    "Recall that points D ∈ S r B can be thought of as formal sumsD = n 1 b 1 + • • • + n k b k with b i ∈ B for i = 1,..., k and r = n 1 + • • • + n k.The Higgs bundle (L, 0, γ) lies above the zero divisor of γ; that is, the formal sum determined by the points b i ∈ B such that γ bi = 0, weighted by the order to which γ vanishes."
  ]
}